						               													<description>A game from the main creative period from Rudi Hoffmann.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player gets a figure (hence the name of the game), made of 4 tiles.&amp;#10;All the tiles are shuffled before game begins and are spread out over the orange squares of the 7 x 7 squares playing zone of the gameboard.&amp;#10;After the tiles have been turned up the players try to reunite the complete figure.&amp;#10;Alternately the single tiles are drawn as far as the player chooses vertically or horizontically.&amp;#10;When 2 or more tiles have been reunited, they draw as one.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Winner is the player who has completed his figure first.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The graphics are as usual in this period from Hoffmann himself.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
